# Flutter Conventions

## Widgets

- Use `StatelessWidget` or `StatefulWidget` -- no raw functions returning widgets
- Named constructors with `const` when possible
- Props passed via constructor parameters with `required` keyword

```dart
class PokemonCard extends StatelessWidget {
  const PokemonCard({
    super.key,
    required this.name,
    required this.spriteUrl,
    required this.onTap,
  });

  final String name;
  final String spriteUrl;
  final VoidCallback onTap;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) { ... }
}
```

## File Organization

- Reusable widgets in `lib/widgets/`
- Route-level screens in `lib/screens/`
- Data models in `lib/models/`
- API and service classes in `lib/services/`
- State management in `lib/providers/`

## State Management

- Use Provider (`ChangeNotifierProvider`) for app-level state
- Keep providers in `lib/providers/`
- Call `notifyListeners()` after state mutations

## Styling

- Use Material 3 theming (`ThemeData` with `ColorScheme.fromSeed`)
- Prefer theme colors over hardcoded values
- Mobile-first responsive design
